ry or Columbia? I would not need to keep it for more than ten days or so. If I could get it by July 1, I would be finished with it before leaving Mt. Carmel. Or I might check the text later, in the proofs. I am delighted you liked my poor Lolita.2





Yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: HENRY ALLEN MOE

CC, 1 p.





Goldwin Smith Hall

Cornell University

Ithaca, NY.

September 24, 1956

Dear Mr. Moe,

Indeed, I have an excellent candidate for a Guggenheim Fellowship. Her name is Sylvia Berkman.